net.vivialconnect.model.account

Class Account

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.vivialconnect.model.VivialConnectResource
      • net.vivialconnect.model.account.Account
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Account
extends VivialConnectResource
    To access the Vivial Connect API, you must have an account. To set up an account, visit Vivial Connect. Every Vivial Connect account has at least one user. You can manage users and accounts using the USERS and ACCOUNTS endpoints in the API. For more info visit: Accounts documentation.

      • update

        public Account update()
               throws VivialConnectException
        Updates this account by sending to the server the properties that were changed via this class's set methods.

        For more details on which properties can be updated, refer to the VivialConnect API documentation's account section.

        If the account you're trying to update does not exist, a VivialConnectException holding a 404 response code will be thrown.

        Returns:
        this instance of Account with the updated properties
        Throws:
        VivialConnectException - if there is an API-level error
